Elizabeth Arden ? the brand has an uncompromising vision to create absolutely the best beauty products that not covered but benefited the feminine skin and body. Elizabeth Arden Green Tea Lotus Eau De Toilette (Women) is one such attempt to make the female skin look younger while keeping it fresh and unharmed. Launched in 2008 as limited edition Green Tea Lotus had the nose of Rodrigo Flores-Roux behind capturing its fragrance. This perfume blends Asian lily cherry blossom yuzu and fruity accords of plum to offer a fresh and reviving aroma. Tender and light this exotic fragrance greets you with lily gracious lotus green tea and osmanthus at the heart. The base notes comprise of musk and white birch to contribute a sensuous woodsy essence.

Elizabeth Arden lived by a fundamental mantra that a woman?s beauty must not just lay in a layer of makeup. She created an intelligent relationship between science and nature through her range of beauty products to help a woman take her natural assets to the notch of finesse. A classic sensuous fragrance from the house of Elizabeth Arden 5Th Avenue After Five Eau De Toilette (Women) reminds you that the night is still young. This misty musky fragrance fills the air around you with energy and romance that makes you expect the unexpected. Elizabeth Arden After Five Perfume starts with top notes of honeysuckle coriander plum and bergamot that lend a vibrant mix of fruity and spicy blast to it. A floral heart with a gracious blend of Indian lotus jasmine saffron and lily-of-the-valley make it all the more passionate. At the base this perfume turns all the more promising with birch sandalwood and Tonka bean intertwined in a distinct manner

Product Description

It is the gleaming pendant set against the black velvet of your evening gown. It is the rising sun peeping at you from between two buildings tickling your arm with its warmth and nourishment. It is the rainbow glow on the bubbles in your flute of clean straw-coloured champagne. It is 5th Avenue Gold. This flanker for the original 5th Avenue is lighter a little sweeter and very subtle. 5th Avenue Gold begins with a pared down combination of bergamot mandarin and lily of the valley adds a guava note to the essential heart of iris jasmine and rose and finally allow you to feel its weight in your hand through a sensual base note of musk.
